			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of 30-year-old Dr. H.L.M. on antisemitism and discrimination in pre-war Hungary, hardships during his labor service, the
					deportation of his unit to the German-Hungarian border in December 1944, forced labor under German command, and a death march in
					the spring of 1945 from Schandorf through the Alps to the Mauthausen and Günskirchen concentration camps.</p>
			</abstract>
